- Your analysis should refer to line numbers.
- For every loop you need to specify the number of iterations and the cost per iteration.
- Each step of the analysis should be justified with one or two sentences.

public final class AsymQ5 {
    static class Node {
        int v;
        Node next;
        Node(int v, Node next) { this.v = v; this.next = next; }
    }

    static Node h;   // head of the linked list

    // Your analysis should be based on the number of nodes N in the linked list with head h.
    public static int f() {
        int s = 0;
        Node p = h;
        while (p != null) {
            s += g(p);
            p = p.next;
        }
        return s;
    }

    private static int g(Node start) {
        int c = 0;
        Node q = start;
        while (q != null) {
            c += q.v;
            q = q.next;
        }
        return c;
    }
}
